    {
        "content": "<p>I was responding to</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"307953\">Ruben Van de Velde</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/First.20steps.20in.20linear.20algebra/near/497290662\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>pi is defined as <code>noncomputable def Real.pi</code>, while <code>2</code> comes from the <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Real.commRing#doc\">docs#Real.commRing</a> instance, which apparently is computable (for whatever good that does)</p>\n</blockquote>",
